Sentencas: In the present work, we report a composite of industrial-grade material LaCePr-oxide (LCP) and perovskite La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) for advanced electrolyte layer-free fuel cells (EFFCs).
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell

Sentencas: The microstructure, morphology, and electrical properties of the LCP, LSCF, and LCP-LSCF composite were investigated and characterized by XRD, SEM, EDS, TEM, and EIS.
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell

Sentencas: Various ratios of LCP to LSCF in the composite were modulated to achieve balanced ionic and electronic conductivities.
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell

Sentencas: Fuel cell with an optimum ratio of 60 wt% LCP to 40 wt% LSCF reached the highest open circuit voltage (OCV) at 1.01 V and a maximum power density of 745 mW cm(-2) at 575 degrees C, also displaying a good performance stability.
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell

Sentencas: The high performance is attributed to the interfacial mechanisms and electrode catalytic effects.
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell

Sentencas: The findings from the present study promote industrial-grade rare-earth oxide as a promising new material for innovative low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC) technology.
Titulo: Industrial-grade rare-earth and perovskite oxide for high-performance electrolyte layer-free fuel cell
